    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix race condition in RA procedure initiation\n\n### Summary\nThere's a race condition in the `initiate_ra_proc` function where multiple threads can simultaneously access and modify the RA processes array without proper synchronization. This can lead to corrupted RA state or crashes under load.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder high RACH load with multiple processing threads, observe:\n- Segfaults in `initiate_ra_proc` or related RA functions\n- Inconsistent RA states where processes appear to be in multiple states simultaneously\n- RNTI allocation conflicts causing connection failures\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/mac.h`: Added pthread.h include and ra_mutex to eNB_MAC_INST\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/main.c`: Initialize the new mutex during MAC setup\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_RA.c`: Protect critical sections with mutex locking in initiate_ra_proc, cancel_ra_proc, clear_ra_proc, and schedule_RA functions\n\nThe fix ensures thread-safe access to the shared RA processes array by wrapping all modification and read operations with proper mutex protection.\n"
}